|
| Scirtothrips. aurantii         | South African citrus thrips      | In Australia, this species has only been found damaging species of Bryophyllum and Kalanchoe . Citrus and mango have not been damaged in Australia. It is present in northern NSW and Qld. |
| Scirtothrips dorsalis*         | Strawberry thrips, chilli thrips | Highly polyphagous including many species from Solanaceae, Fabaceae and Cucurbitaceae. Plants from many other plant families also are hosts.